To obtain an identity token in Artifactory, you can follow these steps:

Log in to Artifactory as a user with sufficient permissions.

Click on your username in the top right corner and select "Edit Profile."

In the "Access Tokens" tab, click on the "New" button.

Enter a name for your token and select the appropriate scope (e.g., read, write, deploy).

Click on "Create" to generate the token.

Copy the token and save it in a secure location.

Frog:

To obtain an identity token in Frog, you can follow these steps:

Log in to Frog as a user with sufficient permissions.

Click on your username in the top right corner and select "Account Settings."

In the "API Tokens" tab, click on the "Generate New Token" button.

Enter a name for your token and select the appropriate permissions (e.g., read-only, read-write).

Click on "Generate Token" to generate the token.

Copy the token and save it in a secure location.
